NexaCore Enterprise Network Topology Project
1.Overview

This project presents the design and implementation of an enterprise network topology for NexaCore, developed as part of an academic assignment.

The objective was to analyze the company's requirements and demands, implement a functional and scalable network solution, and improve upon the base topology provided.

In addition to fulfilling all requested specifications, our team enhanced the original design to ensure better performance, security, and scalability.

2.Project Goals
-Meet all NexaCore's stated network requirements and constraints
-Improve the base topology with optimized architecture
-Ensure high availability and fault tolerance
-Provide a secure and segmented network design
-Deliver a fully reproducible configuration

3.Configuration Files

This project is open-source, and all device configurations are provided in this repository.

✔ Ready-to-use configurations
✔ Copy-paste compatible
✔ Structured per device

You can directly apply the configurations to compatible devices or network simulators (e.g., Packet Tracer, GNS3).

4.Technologies Used
-Cisco-based configurations (CLI)
-VLANs & Trunking (802.1Q)
-OSPF (or chosen routing protocol)
-DHCP & DNS services
-ACLs for traffic control

5.License

This project is released as open-source for educational purposes.
You are free to use, modify, and distribute it.

👥 Authors

Class project developed by students for academic purposes.

FINAL NOTES:

This project demonstrates how a basic network topology can be transformed into a more efficient, secure, and scalable enterprise solution.

All configurations are provided to ensure that anyone can easily replicate and learn from this implementation.